title: Toxic train derailment in Ohio: What to know
description: Weeks after a major train derailment and controlled explosion of chemicals in East Palestine, Ohio, residents have been encouraged to return home. But many questions remain about how the train derailed and what the lingering chemical exposure could be in residents' air and water.

title: Webb telescope uses celestial Pandora's box to see distant galaxies
description: The James Webb Space Telescope just peered into a celestial Pandora's box to see what lies beyond a megacluster of galaxies.

title: Tensions mount at the Belarusian-Ukrainian border amid concerns of Russian spring offensive
description: Tensions are mounting at the border between Ukraine and Moscow-allied Belarus, as officials in Kyiv warn of a Russian spring offensive amid ramped-up military attacks from the Kremlin.

title: Wild celebrations get underway as Kansas City Chiefs take to the streets for Super Bowl parade
description: It was party time in Missouri on Tuesday as the Chiefs continued their celebrations after Sunday's Super Bowl win with a parade through the streets of Kansas City.

title: Raquel Welch, 'Fantastic Voyage' star, has died at age 82
description: Raquel Welch, a veteran actress who rose to fame in the 1960s in the films "One Million Years B.C." and "Fantastic Voyage," has died, according to a statement provided by her manager, Steve Sauer.

title: Expert: Trump's legal peril is deepening
description: Federal prosecutors investigating former President Donald Trump's handling of classified documents have asked a court to force his attorney, Evan Corcoran, to provide additional testimony, two sources familiar with the Justice Department's motion told CNN. CNN legal analyst Norm Eisen explains the significance of the decision.

title: Rihanna and A$AP Rocky are embracing parenthood: 'We're best friends with a baby'
description: It's a new era for pop superstar Rihanna and her partner, rapper A$AP Rocky, is along for the ride.

title: What Stalin's daughter taught me
description: North Korean dictator Kim Jong Un was back in the spotlight last week after appearing at two lavish military events in Pyongyang. In one photograph, he is seen with his generals reviewing a midnight parade of ballistic missiles. Beside him stands his roughly 9-year-old daughter.

title: The world's largest outdoor ice rink is closed due to lack of ice
description: First it was ski resorts not being able to operate due to the climate crisis. Now, the world's largest outdoor ice rink is facing the possibility of a season fully closed, due to a lack of ice.

title: What 'China's Hawaii' has to do with the appearance of alleged spy balloons across the globe
Escaped zoo owl learns to hunt in Central Park
description: Escaped owl becomes a celebrity and learns to catch rats. CNN's Jeanne Moos reports New Yorkers DO give a hoot.

title: Armie Hammer's ex-wife Elizabeth Chambers to host show about toxic relationships
description: Armie Hammer's ex-wife Elizabeth Chambers is set to host and executive produce a series about toxic relationships.

title: Nikki Haley delivers her first 2024 presidential campaign pitch
description: Former South Carolina Republican Gov. Nikki Haley delivered her first 2024 campaign pitch Wednesday in her home state after announcing her run for president.

title: Husband of prominent Iranian human rights lawyer summoned by judiciary
description: The husband of prominent Iranian human rights lawyer Nasrin Sotoudeh will be forced to serve the rest of a five-year prison sentence, Sotoudeh told CNN on Tuesday.

title: Top Republicans plot Santos' ouster as embattled freshman weighs reelection
description: Embattled Rep. George Santos is contemplating a nightmare scenario for House Republicans: Trying to stick it out in Congress, even if he is indicted on criminal charges.

title: World's oldest Hebrew Bible could fetch $50 million at auction
description: A  Hebrew Bible more than 1,000 years old and described as "one of the most important and singular texts in human history" will go on show later this month, before going under the hammer.

title: Elon Musk donated $1.9 billion of Tesla stock to charity last year
description: Tesla CEO Elon Musk gave 11.5 million shares of his stake in the electric automaker to an undisclosed charity last year, shares worth about $1.9 billion at the time they were donated.

title: Mother pulls kids from daycare after controversial Black History Month activity
description: A mother in Miami says she was shocked and outraged after the staff at her children's daycare shared photos with parents of students in blackface as part of Black History Month. CNN national correspondent Athena Jones reports.

title: 'Staircase' ice and deep cracks under so-called Doomsday Glacier could set the stage for collapse, scientists say
description: Antarctica's "Doomsday Glacier" -- nicknamed because its collapse could drive catastrophic sea level rise -- is melting rapidly in unexpected ways, according to new research.

title: Rebel Wilson launching 'Fluid' dating app
description: Rebel Wilson wants to help people find the "kind of love with no labels."

title: Barclays shares plunge 10% as profit falls
description: Shares of Barclays tumbled nearly 10% Wednesday after the British bank reported a sharp drop in profit, driven by increased provisions for bad debts and huge fines for wrongly sold securities in the United States.

title: Former Philadelphia Eagles captain Chris Maragos awarded $43.5 million in medical malpractice case
description: Former Philadelphia Eagles captain Chris Maragos has been awarded $43.5 million in a lawsuit against his doctors over a career-ending knee injury.

title: Deadly earthquake leaves deep chasm in middle of olive grove
description: An olive grove in Turkey's Hatay province was split in two during last week's devastating earthquake, creating a 130-foot-deep canyon.

title: 'Star Trek: Picard' reunites the old crew for its 'Generation'-al third and final season
description: After a pair of slow-going voyages that sought to blend old and new, "Star Trek: Picard" warps back to its roots in a third and final season filled with familiar "The Next Generation" faces. While building the show around its AARP-eligible cast two decades after the last movie imposes certain limits, getting the band back together feels like a clear case of giving the loyal audience what it wants.

title: Cleveland Clinic to open its third London facility as Brits flock to private health care
description: US group Cleveland Clinic will open its third London facility this autumn as demand for private health care booms in the United Kingdom — sparked in large part by long wait times to access treatment on the National Health Service (NHS).

title: Family of unarmed Black man sues the Louisiana officer who killed him while waiting for release of body-camera video
description: The family of an unarmed Black man who was shot and killed by a Shreveport, Louisiana, police officer has filed a federal wrongful death lawsuit against the officer.

title: CNN reports from largest trauma hospital in the Turkish quake zone
description: CNN chief medical correspondent Dr. Sanjay Gupta goes inside the largest trauma hospital in the Turkish earthquake zone.

title: 'Eggs-travagent theft': Man convicted of stealing nearly 200,000 chocolate eggs
description: A man has been convicted of stealing nearly 200,000 chocolate eggs, worth around £40,000 ($48,000), in what British police have dubbed an "eggs-travagent theft."

title: Lady Gaga in first look of 'Joker' sequel
description: Lady Gaga looks to be off the deep end with her new character.

title: Lufthansa IT failure grounds flights worldwide
description: German airline Lufthansa has been hit by a company-wide IT outage that has caused a raft of flight cancellations and delays and left thousands of passengers stranded in airports.

title: Brand new Boeing 747 scrapped after 16 flights
description: A Boeing 747 configured as a private VIP jet is being scrapped after having spent just 30 hours in service over 16 flights.

title: Thousands of people can't get full treatments of a lifesaving cancer drug

title: Russian offensive in east Ukraine 'more aspirational than realistic,' Western officials say
description: As Russia begins a new offensive in eastern Ukraine, the US and its allies are skeptical Moscow has amassed the manpower and resources to make significant gains, US, UK and Ukrainian officials tell CNN. "It's likely more aspirational than realistic," said a senior US military official.

title: Elderly protest health insurance cuts in China's Wuhan
description: A protest broke out in central China's Wuhan on Wednesday as elderly residents showed their discontent with a local government reform to public health insurance that came into effect earlier this month.

title: These feats of architecture have been named the best of the year
description: The world's newest architectural showstoppers include a birdhouse-covered hotel suite suspended in the woods of Harads, Sweden; Sydney's $230-million transformation of a naval bunker into an arts complex; and a futuristic sports stadium in China's Zhejiang Province designed to mimic nearby mountainous terrain, according to Architectural Digest (AD).

title: Former world No. 8 Jack Sock stunned by full-time finance professional in Florida tournament

title: Elon Musk wants to find someone to replace him at Twitter by year-end
description: Elon Musk is aiming to "find someone else" to run Twitter by the end of this year.

title: Duangphet Phromthep, one of 12 boys rescued from a Thai cave in 2018, dies in UK
description: Duangphet Phromthep, one of the 12 boys rescued from a flooded Thai cave after a weekslong operation that drew global attention in 2018, has died in the UK, British and Thai officials announced Wednesday.

description: Sébastien Haller had big boots to fill.

description: Nicola Sturgeon, Scotland's First Minister and the figurehead of the faltering Scottish independence movement, is set to resign, UK media reported Wednesday.

description: The European Union is setting up a working group to examine whether frozen Russian assets can be used to rebuild Ukraine.

title: Nikki Haley to push for a 'renewal of American pride' in first 2024 campaign pitch
description: Former United Nations Ambassador Nikki Haley is expected to say that not enough Americans feel proud of their country and that it's time for a new generation of leadership when she makes her opening pitch for the Republican nomination for president Wednesday, according to a person familiar with her thinking.

title: The Taylor Swift of Amsterdam
description: If you were to ask the tragically bored 17-year-old Euny whether it would be a Depeche Mode concert or a Johannes Vermeer exhibit that would give middle-aged Euny a full-on panic attack in a huntdown for their tickets, she would never have guessed the answer would be "both." Nor would she have believed that the one that mattered more—and the one that was harder to come by—was the Vermeer.

title: Aaron Rodgers is starting his darkness retreat this week -- and he might film it
description: Green Bay Packers quarterback Aaron Rodgers is preparing to undertake his darkness retreat, which will take place at the "end of this week."
